# Buttermilk Pancakes

> This is a simple recipe for buttermilk Pancakes

## Dry Ingredients

- Flour | 2 cups | 
- Baking Powder | 2 tsp | 
- Sugar | 2 tbsp | 
- Salt | 3/4 tsp | 

Sift together dry ingredients.

## Wet Ingredients

- Butter | 2 tbsp | Melted
- Eggs | 2 | 
- Buttermilk | 2 cup | 

Separate egg yokes from whites, and mix yokes with buttermilk in a second bowl. Add in melted butter after having let cool for a few minutes.

Create well in dry ingredients and pour in contents of wet ingredients bowl. Mix till homogeneous. Let batter sit for 10 min.

Wip egg whites till frothy and fold into batter.

Heat pan to medium/high.

Use ice cream scoop-sized spoon to ladle batter into heated pan. Pancakes should be about 3-4" in diameter. Cook till golden brown on each side.